---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Document the maths so the eggs are reproducible.
const letters = [
  ['P', 80],
  ['a', 97],
  ['p', 112],
  ['p', 112],
  ['o', 111],
  ['l', 108],
];
const sum = letters.reduce((acc, [, n]) => acc + (n as number), 0); // 620
const hue = sum % 360; // 260
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Easter Eggs"
  description="The hidden things built into this site, and the maths behind them."
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">You found it</p>
    <h1>Easter eggs</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      The whole site is quietly built around my nickname, <strong>Pappol</strong>.
      Here's everything that's hidden, and the maths behind it.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- Egg 1: the colour -->
  <section class="egg">
    <h2>1 · The signature colour is computed from “Pappol”</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      “Pappol” can't be a literal hex code — <code>P</code>, <code>o</code> and
      <code>l</code> aren't hex digits. So instead the colour is
      <em>derived</em> from the name's character codes:
    </p>
    <div class="calc">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Letter</th>{letters.map(([l]) => <th>{l}</th>)}<th>Σ</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="muted">ASCII</td>
            {letters.map(([, n]) => <td>{n}</td>)}
            <td><strong>{sum}</strong></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="formula">
        <code>{sum} mod 360 = {hue}°</code> → hue <strong>{hue}°</strong> → indigo.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="muted">
      Every accent, gradient and highlight on the site is built on
      <code>hue {hue}</code>. Change the single <code>--pappol-hue</code> value in
      the CSS and the entire site re-skins itself.
    </p>
    <div class="swatch-row" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="swatch" style={`background:hsl(${hue} 72% 55%)`}></span>
      <span class="swatch" style={`background:hsl(${hue} 80% 74%)`}></span>
      <span class="swatch" style={`background:hsl(${hue} 72% 46%)`}></span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Egg 2: timing -->
  <section class="egg">
    <h2>2 · The animation timing comes from “Pappol” too</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      The same sum drives motion. <code>{sum} → 0.{sum}</code> gives the easing
      curve <code>cubic-bezier(0.62, 0, 0.38, 1)</code> (with
      <code>0.38 = 1 − 0.62</code>), and the base transition duration is
      <code>{hue}ms</code> — the hue value, reused as milliseconds. Hover any
      card or button to feel it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Egg 3: type pappol -->
  <section class="egg">
    <h2>3 · Type <code>pappol</code> anywhere</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      Type the six letters <code>p-a-p-p-o-l</code> on any page (not in a text
      field) to trigger <strong>Pappol mode</strong>: confetti and a full
      hue-spin of the site's colour, settling back to {hue}°.
    </p>
    <button class="btn btn--primary" id="try-pappol" type="button">Try it now</button>
  </section>

  <!-- Egg 4: console -->
  <section class="egg">
    <h2>4 · A message in the developer console</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      Open your browser's DevTools console on any page and there's a styled
      greeting waiting — with a nudge toward this very page.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Egg 5: hidden door -->
  <section class="egg">
    <h2>5 · The hidden door</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      This page isn't in the menu. There are two ways in: typing
      <code>pappol</code> (egg 3) shows a link, and the little full-stop after
      my name in the footer — <code>© … Riccardo Parola<strong>.</strong></code>
      — is secretly a link here.
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="muted closing">More may appear over time. Keep poking around. 👀</p>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  document.getElementById('try-pappol')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    // @ts-ignore - exposed by /scripts/easter-eggs.js
    if (window.__pappolMode) window.__pappolMode();
  });
</script>

<style>
  .page-head { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .page-head h1 { margin: 0.3rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .egg {
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .egg h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0 0 0.6rem; }
  .calc {
    background: var(--bg-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
  .calc table { border-collapse: collapse; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .calc th, .calc td {
    padding: 0.3rem 0.7rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .formula { margin: 0.8rem 0 0; }
  .swatch-row { display: flex; gap: 0.6rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .swatch {
    width: 48px; height: 48px; border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .closing { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
</style>
